sub_title: Groundwater Specialist | PhD Candidate at Delft University of Technology
summary: I am a PhD researcher at TU Delft, where my work is focused on the influence of hydrology on the occurrence of landslides in the Ecuadorian Andes. More specifically, on landslide occurrence within the reservoir that is created by the hydropower dams in southeast Ecuador. Due to the lack of in-situ data, we analyze ground movement data derived from satellites.
